SIMPLE: livelong
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Livelong
<hw>Live"long`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>lifelong</ets>. Cf. <er>Lifelong</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Whole; entire; long in passing; -- used of time, as day or night,
in adverbial phrases, and usually with a sense of tediousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The obscure bird⟦br⟧
Clamored the <qex>livelong</qex> night.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How could she sit the <qex>livelong</qex> day,⟦br⟧
Yet never ask us once to play?</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lasting; durable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou hast built thyself a <qex>livelong</qex> monument.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lively</ent>⟦br⟧
